# ─── Shared saved-state (hearts + SRP) via Upstash Redis ────────────────────
# These wire "♥ heart a powder" + editable SRP so they persist REMOTELY and
# sync to everyone using the site (instead of a local-only file).
#
# Provision (free tier: 256 MB, 500,000 commands/month):
#   Vercel → Storage → Marketplace → "Upstash for Redis" → create → Connect to
#   this project. Vercel then injects these vars into the deployment automatically.
#
# For local dev, get the values one of these ways:
#   • vercel env pull .env.local         (after linking the project), or
#   • copy them from the Upstash console (Redis database → REST API), or
#   • cp .env.example .env.local and paste them in.
# Then restart `npm run dev`. (No creds = falls back to local .data/state.json,
# which does NOT sync to anyone.)
#
# The app accepts EITHER naming below — set whichever pair your store exposes.

# Upstash-native (Upstash console / newer Marketplace integration):
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=

# …or Vercel-KV-style (legacy KV / some Marketplace setups) — leave blank if unused:
# KV_REST_API_URL=
# KV_REST_API_TOKEN=
